\begin{abstract}
A multi-channel atomic magnetometer operating in an unshielded environment is described and characterised. The magnetometer is based on D$_1$ optical pumping and D$_2$ polarimetry of Cs vapour contained in gas-buffered cells. Several technical implementations are described and discussed in detail. The demonstrated sensitivity of the setup is  $100 \, \mbox{fT}/\sqrt{\mbox{Hz}}$ when operating in the difference mode.
\end{abstract}



















